{
  "texts": [
    "Specifically, the tensor containing audio features typically has its own distinct feature dimension.",
    "The audio feature embedding Z a is projected into a vector with the same dimensionality as the text embedding using a projection function w(•):H a = w(Z a), where H a denotes the projected audio embedding in the text embedding space.",
    "These audio embeddings are then concatenated with the input text embedding H t to form a new embedding sequence that integrates both speech and text information:H = [H a, H t].",
    "This combined sequence is then fed into the LLM.",
    "Some researchers have also implicitly incorporated the projection step within the original encoder, achieving modality projection by adjusting the encoder's parameters during training [37].Most models use a multi-layer perceptron (MLP) as the projection module, while some adopt more complex techniques such as Q-Former, which introduces trainable query tokens that attend to audio features and output fixed-length embeddings aligned with the LLM input space [26]."
  ]
}